EOH has announced the acquisition of the Cornastone group of companies, subject to regulatory approval. Cornastone’s business offerings include support services to telecommunications network operators in the areas of call centre operations, billing operations, revenue assurance, and operational data analysis. The company also provides application managed services to its customers, along with unique revenue management and revenue protection solutions using billing systems and big data insights. Cornastone has an annual turnover in excess of R300 million and employs 280 people. “Cornastone is a recognised leader in its field, and has an extremely strong management team and a skilled employee base,” said EOH CEO Asher Bohbot. “The Cornastone basket of offerings enhances EOH’s existing service offerings and improves EOH’s capability in the market place.”